{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">component.isStopping()\n</pre><ul><li>Returns a boolean indicating whether the component is currently in the <strong>process of stopping.</strong></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>This function is useful for <strong>graceful shutdown handling.</strong> You can use it inside long-running scripts or loops to check if the component is stopping, allowing you to <strong>clean up resources</strong> or <strong>exit early.</strong></li><li>When <code>true</code>, the component is in the process of stopping <span style=\"color: rgb(23, 43, 77);\">—</span> usually because:</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">The user stopped the component via the UI,</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">The component is shutting down as part of a system stop.</li><li>When <code>false</code>, the component is running normally.</li><li><strong>Best practice:</strong> Always check <code>component.isStopping()</code> in loops or long-running operations to prevent incomplete shutdowns or hanging tasks.</li></ul><h3><br></h3><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li><code>true</code> if the component is currently stopping, <code>false</code> otherwise <em><u>(bool)</u></em>.</li></ul><h3><br></h3><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">-- Example of graceful shutdown inside a loop\nfor i = 1, 1000 do\n    if component.isStopping() then\n        trace(\"Component is stopping, exiting loop.\")\n        break\n    end\n    -- Simulate work\n    trace(\"Processing item: \" .. i)\nend\n</pre>",
    "Name": "component.isStopping",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Checks whether the current component is in the stopping state."
}